title: fourth_wall
body:
The imaginary "wall" that separates a piece of fiction from the real-life audience.

This tag is used when that wall is "broken" by the characters involved indicating they realize that they are set in fiction, usually by addressing the audience or interacting with elements of the medium, such as grabbing a speech bubble, manipulating the panels of a comic, and similar actions.

[[Deadpool]] in particular is known for his constant breaking of the fourth wall.

The pixiv tag is "メタ発言 (meta quote).":http://www.pixiv.net/search.php?s_mode=s_tag_full&word=%E3%83%A1%E3%82%BF%E7%99%BA%E8%A8%80 However, "[[meta]]" tag on danbooru has a bit different meaning.

h4. See also

* [[against fourth wall]]
* [[through medium]]
** [[through screen]]
** [[through painting]]
** [[through page]]

title: c-3po
body:
A fictional [[humanoid robot]] from the [[Star Wars]] franchise.

The [b]C-3P0[/b] [[protocol droid]] appears in the first Star War film from 1977. Since then he has been played by English actor "Anthony Daniels":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anthony_Daniels on each and every Star Wars movie and other related media.

The character was designed by "Ralph McQuarrie":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ralph_McQuarrie in the 70s. According to him, C-3PO was based in the [[Maschinenmensch]] android from the 1927 silent sci-fi film [[Metropolis (Fritz Lang)]].

h4.See also

* [[R2-D2]]

title: konpaku_youmu
body:
The "Half-Human Half-Phantom". Stage 5 boss of [[Touhou]]'s [[Perfect Cherry Blossom]] and later a recurring playable character.

Gardener of [[Hakugyokurou]], the netherworld pagoda, and bodyguard of its "princess", [[Saigyouji Yuyuko]]. She wields a [[katana]], Roukanken, and a [[wakizashi]], Hakurouken. Youmu specializes in rapid swordplay taught by her predecessor [[Konpaku Youki|Youki]]. She is always followed by [[Konpaku Youmu (ghost)|her phantom half]], which floats beside her. She is nicknamed "Myon" in many fanworks, based on a [[myon (phrase)|nonsensical word]] she muttered back in PCB. Ironically, although she is half-phantom, she is terrified of ghosts.

title: kaya-chan_wa_kowakunai
body:
A 2022-to-Present seinen supernatural action manga series by Yuritaro.

The series follows the kindergartner [[Satou Kaya]] and the kindergarten teacher [[Hasumi Chie]]. Kaya is an odd girl who seems to constantly get into arguments and fights with her peers. As Kaya is a daily troublemaker, Chie-sensei gets assigned to have to watch her closely during work. Things get complicated though when Chie-sensei ends up discovering that Kaya's behavior comes from her actually protecting everyone from the supernatural.

h4. External links

title: rei_(cookie)
body:
Voice of [[Kirisame Marisa]] in [[Cookie (Touhou)|Cookie☆☆ S3]] and [[Onozuka Komachi]] in Halloween☆. Typically portrayed in her kaoru式 MMD model which is based on Forbidden Scrollery's Marisa, wearing a [[black coat]] with [[buttons]], [[black gloves]], a [[petticoat]], and a [[purple bow|purple]] [[hair bow]]. Extremely commonly depicted as a [[genderswap (ftm)|male]] [[crossdressing]] [[trap]] due to her husky voice.

Despite having a similar voice to [[Azusa (cookie)|]] and [[Mars (cookie)|]], she is far worse at singing which became popular in its own way. 

Because of how often Rei is depicted as male, identifying their gender solely based on the image can be difficult or impossible. If the artist has tagged the image or written commentary with RIくん or RI君, then they are a male. Other hints can be: [[Sananana (cookie)|]] creeping on them, the artist drawing Rei as male in previous images, or the comments on the image. If there is absolutely no indication of Rei being male, then tag them as female.

h4. Appearance

* !asset #21018311: Profile

title: suzu_(cookie)
body:
Voice of [[Kirisame Marisa]] in [[Atouda Ako (character)|]]'s [[Cookie (Touhou)|Kuso☆☆☆]]. Recognizable for her nearly always [[closed eyes]], [[star (symbol)|]]s on her vest instead of buttons, and a [[red bow]] in her hair. Her [[witch hat]] sometimes [[living clothes|comes alive]] too. Known for having the worst microphone of all of Kuso. Escaped Cookie fairly quickly so all of her jokes are either from the voice drama or were made up afterwards in MADs and fan art. 

While [[Hinase (cookie)|]] is depicted as a yandere, [[Rurima (cookie)|]] as permanently angry, and [[Noel (cookie)|]] as cold and distant, Suzu is the murderous psycopath. This started as in the voice drama Marisa completely ignored Reimu's feeling for her, but morphed into a general lack of empathy. She started to get drawn with [[knife|knives]] and [[chainsaw]]s and covered in [[blood]], especially hunting after [[JOKER (cookie)|]]. In contrast she is depicted as extremely flustered by anything romantic or sexual.

No one really knows why Suzu and JOKER are shipped together so often. Suzu at one point made a joke about her parents thought she was a lesbian in high school, but other than that it is a mystery to all.

title: uzuki_(cookie)
body:
Voice of [[Kirisame Marisa]] in the original [[cookie_(touhou)|Cookie☆]]. Distinguishable by having her [[side braid]] on her right side of her head with a [[pink bow|pink]] [[hair bow|bow]], [[yellow eyes]], and her [[red-framed eyewear|red]] [[glasses]]. Also called Marina (her real name). Essentially the main character of Cookie, she was the one to recruit other members like [[Reu (cookie)|]] and [[Yamin (cookie)|]], the first criticized for her acting, and the first to expose [[Hazuna Rio]] causing the ensuing drama. Left the internet in 2011, but still in contact with Reu.

Usually appears as the main character in MADs due to the large amount of material she recorded. Almost all Marisas are called UDKs in reference to her, partially because her disappearance meant that the others had to live up to her. 

She spawned numerous running jokes:
* "Aaaaaaaaaah, wasureteta!" (Aaaaaaaaaah, I forgot!): Her line when she realized to forgot to reciprocate Alice's gift for Valentine's day.
* [[Van Houten]] cocoa: What she says makes Alice's brownies good.
* Tororo [[soba]] press conference: Her breakdown on a livestream when she was ranting about malicious comments sounded like she was slurping noodles.
* Starry Sky: A poem she wrote. See post #4488363
* Art college ball: A painting she made when applying to art school. Usually appears in the background of other images.
* !asset #21030926
* Assassin UDK: Her [[black hoodie|black]] and [[white hoodie|white]] [[striped hoodie]] she wore during a stream
* Comiket UDK: A possible photo of her as [[Usami Renko]] at Comiket. Whether or not it is actually her is unknown.
* Iwana / Charfish: A soramimi pun during one of her livestreams.

h4. Appearance

* !asset #21030698: Profile
* !asset #21030951: Briefly lived twitter trend

title: yuuhi_(cookie)
body:
One of the voices of [[Kirisame Marisa]] in [[Atouda Ako (character)|]]'s [[cookie_(touhou)|Kuso☆☆☆☆]]. Is a bit touch and go with the Cookie community, but creates new accounts every now and then to answer questions. Her popularity also comes and goes since she tried to organize a voice drama but it fell through after some internal controversy. Identifiable by her [[sleeves past fingers]], slanted [[black eyes]], and [[blue bow|blue]] [[hat bow]]. Almost always paired with [[Meguru (cookie)|]]. 

Her design is theoretically based on [[Uzuki (cookie)|]]'s but there is almost no resemblance. By far Yuuhi's most common appearance is as a companion of some kind to Meguru. Sometimes this is interpreted as [[yuri]], a kid and their [[monster girl|pet monster]], or just as friends. [[Monsterification]] of her is because of her strange eyes and the fact you never see her hands, started by [[tenten_(nicoseiga18696142)|]].

h4. Appearance

* !asset #21075139: Profile
* !asset #21075140: twitter icon

title: meguru_(cookie)
body:
One of the voices of [[Kirisame Marisa]] in [[Atouda Ako (character)|]]'s [[cookie_(touhou)|Kuso☆☆☆☆]], by far the most popular one. Didn't really understand the Cookie community before agreeing to be in the voice drama. Has stayed relatively silent since then, largely disappearing by 2016. 

Her design is based on [[Azusa (cookie)|]]'s, with a [[red bow|red]] [[hat bow]], a [[red bowtie]], [[blue eyes]] with [[white pupils]], very distinct [[blush stickers]] and are sometimes mistaken for [[extra mouth]]s, [[black gloves|black]] [[elbow gloves]], a [[black capelet]], a [[black vest]], and a [[brown apron|brown]] [[waist apron]]. She initially wasn't a very popular character, but her natural pairing with [[Yuuhi (cookie)|]] expanded both of their popularities. 

Starting in 2017, MADs of her started to get created by various people on NicoNico, but the big breakthrough happened with a remix of "Logic Airforce":[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GBPnA2BgqLg] by [[Hirasawa Susumu]] of [[P-Model]]. Another remix of "LAB=01":[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pmcvRQdIn-Y] became even more popular and an [[UTAU]] called MGRoid was created which sounded surprisingly good. Since then, MGR became Cookie's representative in the vocal synth community with extremely high popularity in the Chinese Cookie community on BiliBili. She was dubbed "Hirasawa's Daughter" and has been remixed singing all of his most famous songs. Besides MGRoid, a few other running jokes appear:
* Misreading MGR as maguro ([[tuna]]) or [[Metal Gear Rising: Revengeance]]
* Mistaking her [[blush stickers]] as [[extra mouth]]s, complimenting the monstrous [[Yuuhi (cookie)|]]
* Her mangling Souraze「そうらぜ」 as Soudaze「そうだぜ」: Compared to [[Miura Daisenpai]]'s so~dayo line
* [[Fake Meguru (cookie)|]]: a derivative character that only bears a passing resemblance, started in 2022 by Atouda Ako

h4. Appearance

title: gundam_heavyarms_custom
body:
[b]XXXG-01H2 Gundam Heavyarms Custom[/b]
An improved version of the [[Gundam Heavyarms]], made more suitable for space combat. Not many changes were made, other than the mighty Gatling being replaced by the Twin Gatling Gun for extra destructive potential. The [[Gundam Wing: Endless Waltz|Endless Waltz]] version takes the upgrades a step further by removing the shield and knife, but adding a second set of chest guns, more missiles, and doubling up on the Twin Gatlings for a pair of them on each hand. Alternatively, the MS's colors change to a dark grey with dark green highlights. Its pilot, however, remains the stoic and collected [[Trowa Barton]].

title: gundam_combat
body:
A short-lived [[Gundam]] card game released between 1996 and 1997. The game featured SD [[mobile suit]]s, with the first release featuring mobile suits from [[Gundam wing|Wing]], [[after war Gundam X|X]], [[G Gundam|G]] and [[Mobile suit Gundam|MSG]]. The second release added mobile suits from [[Gundam 08th Ms team|08th MS Team]], [[Gundam 0080|0080]], [[Gundam 0083|0083]], [[zeta Gundam|Zeta]], [[Gundam ZZ|ZZ]], [[char's Counterattack|CCA]], [[victory Gundam|Victory]], and [[Gundam Wing: Endless Waltz|Wing EW]].

While the game has been largely forgotten, it's somewhat notable for featuring a variety of new original variants for the mobile suits featured in the first set . 

Official card illustrations are by [[Taiga Hiroyuki]].

* "Carddass20: Gundam Combat":[http://carddas20.seesaa.net/article/305707007.html]

title: hospital_gown
body:
A type of uniformed clothing provided by hospitals for patients, also know as a patient gown. There're mainly two variants. The loose detachable robe for patients undergoing operations or examinations. The [[pajamas]]-like buttoned top-and-bottom set for hospitalized patients, often [[vertical stripes|vertically striped]]. Their designs are not very standardized, versions often vary in details. The most common colors are blue and white, pink is also somewhat common.

Patients can often be seen with an [[iv stand]] and an [[intravenous drip]].

Not to be confused with [[medical scrubs]], a type of medical gown for medical workers during operations.

Not to be confused with [[bathrobe]].

h4. Examples

* !post #9767936: detachable gown, open front
* !post #7465097: detachable gown, open back
* !post #6675924: detachable set
* !post #6596407: buttoned set, striped
* !post #9755962: detachable gown, pink

title: furry
body:
Anthropomorphic animals. Body fur, feathers, or scales are common. Characters that have only tails or ears are not considered furry, use [[kemonomimi mode]] instead.

"Kemono" is the Japanese equivalent of the term "furry", with fans of such being called "kemona" or "kemoner". Just like with furries in the west, there are numerous subcategories and subcultures within.

[[Monster girl]]s or [[animal ears|kemonomimi]] with a human face [b]do not qualify[/b] for the furry tag (see post #113417 for more information).

h4. Furry scale

* !post #717380: [[animal ears|1]] and [[animal|5]] are [b]not[/b] furry. 2 through [[chibikemo|4]] are.

title: mori_nagayoshi_(fate)
body:
Berserker-class Servant of [[Major Matou]] in the manga [i][[koha-ace|Fate/KOHA-ACE]][/i]. He also appears in [[Fate/Grand Order]] during the [[GUDAGUDA Final Honnouji 2019]] event. In [[Fate/type Redline]], he is summoned by [[Magatsu Reiji]].

He wears a large suit of red [[armor]] that has maneuverable cables hanging from it. Underneath his [[helmet]], he has [[spiked hair|spiked]] [[red hair]] swept over an eye. His Noble Phantasm is the double-edged [[spear]] [[Ningen Mukotsu (fate)|]] (Boneless Man), which is said to cut through any armor.

[[Mysterious Ranmaru X (fate)|]] is a version of his younger brother Mori Ranmaru from the [[Servant Universe (fate)|]]. He's also known by the nickname "Demon Musashi".

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[Keikenchi]], [[Dd (vktr4837)|]]

body:

title: kuriyama_aiko
body:
Series: [[Mitsudomoe (manga)|]]
Also called: Kuriyamacchi

The Marui triplets' school nurse. In looks and personality, she's every man's dream, especially [[Yabe Satoshi|Yabecchi]]'s -- but she's also a complete airhead who misunderstands things easily (even for a Mitsudomoe character) and is so [[clumsy|clumsy]] she's guaranteed to kill anyone who stands nearby for too long.

body: An incredibly unlucky and clumsy worker at Sutegoro Inc. Her name is derived from the Japanese word for "clumsy" ([[clumsy]]).

title: colette_brunel
body:
The main heroine of [[Tales of Symphonia]], and [[Lloyd Irving|Lloyd]]'s childhood friend/primary love interest. The Chosen of Mana of the world of Sylvarant, beneath Colette's [[clumsy]] exterior lies a responsible young girl who would go to extremes to make sure her friends do not worry about her. Her seiyuu is [[Mizuki Nana]].

title: okuda_nao
body:
A [i][[K-ON! High School]][/i] character, she debuted after the April 2011 manga relaunch. An incoming freshman and light music club member at Sakuragaoka High School, she was initially known only as Okuda-san. 

Since she is too clumsy for physical activities, she joined as a last resort. However, as a [[clumsy]], she can't play instruments either. Because all she can do is study, she eventually became well-versed in music theory and learned how to use music creation software on the suggestion of [[Yamanaka Sawako]].

She is a member of [[Wakaba Girls (k-on!)|]] with [[Nakano Azusa]], [[Hirasawa Ui]], [[Suzuki Jun]], and [[Saitou Sumire]], and is the group's songwriter and producer.

title: gundam_wing:_frozen_teardrop
body:
A novel series in the [[Gundam Wing]] continuity, set decades after [[Gundam Wing: Endless Waltz|Endless Waltz]].

The series is somewhat notorious for featuring a cast largely comprised of descendants and clones of the original series' cast, and that almost of it's original [[mobile suit]]s are either not illustrated or only depicted wearing cloaks to obscure their appearance ([[Gundam Prometheus]] being the only exception until the [[Wing Gundam Snow White Prelude]] figure was released).

title: ibaraki_douji_(fate)
body:
An [[oni]] Berserker-class Servant appearing in [[Fate/Grand Order]], first appearing as a boss in the [[Kikoku Suimu Makyou Rashoumon]] event before being introduced as a playable servant in the [[Tenma Otogizoushi Onigashima]] event.

Her Noble Phantasm is Rashoumon Dai Engi. Has red-tinted hands and feet, and carries a bone sword. The first "Raid Boss" in Fate/Grand Order, her story is later expanded upon in the [[Tenma Otogizoushi Onigashima]] and [[Halloween Comeback!|Halloween 2016]] (where it is revealed that she secretly likes sweets) events. Holds a deep grudge against [[Watanabe no Tsuna (fate)|]] for cutting off her hand, in the original mythology.

She is nicknamed "banana oni" by the fanbase due to her overall yellow color scheme and her wide forehead which seamlessly transitioned into her hair, giving her a very smooth forehead.

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[Hidari (Left Side)|]]
[b]Voice Actress:[/b] [[Touyama Nao]]

title: arjuna_alter_(fate)
body:
Berserker-class Servant seen in [[Fate/Grand Order]]. An [[Alter servant|Alter]] version of [[Arjuna (Fate)|]].

He has [[silver hair|silver]] or [[black hair]], [[grey eyes|grey]] or [[brown eyes]], [[dark skin]], [[horns]], [[wings]] and a [[tail]]. Wears [[pants]] and [[boots]] across all Ascensions.

[spoiler]Arjuna Alter is the result of the entire Hindu Pantheon (sans Kama/Mara) conglomerating in the body of the hero Arjuna. Appears as one of the main villains of Lostbelt nr. 4: Yugakshetra. Arjuna Alter is the king of the Indian Lostbelt; having been manipulated by [[Ashiya Douman (Fate)|Ashiya Douman]], he has been accelerating the Saṃsāra of Genesis and Terminus to the point of time-space growing unstable, all for the sake of a perfect world without evil.

When he finally fights his rival and half-brother [[Karna (fate)|]] in the climactic showdown, Arjuna Alter loses his usual cool and becomes dead-set on exterminating Karna once and for all.[/spoiler]

title: alina_gray
body:
A character in [[Magia Record: Mahou Shoujo Madoka Magica Gaiden]] and one of the three leaders of the Wings of Magius. Her [[Doppel (madoka magica)|]] form is [[Old Dorothy]]/[[Neo Dorothy Motherfucker]]. Often seen with her kouhai [[Misono Karin]].

She has [[aqua eyes]], [[small breasts]], and [[very long hair|very long]] [[straight hair|straight]] [[green hair]] with a yellow [[streaked hair|streak]], [[sidelocks]], [[blunt ends]] and a [[hair between eyes|lock between her eyes]].

In her daily life she wears the [[Sakae General School uniform]], accessorized with a [[loose bowtie]], [[sleeves rolled up]], [[red wristband|red]] [[wristband]]s, a [[side-tie shirt]], a [[belt pouch]] with a [[paint stains|paint-stained]] [[cleaning rag]] and [[loose socks|loose]] [[white socks|white]] [[socks]]. Her hair is also tied into a [[single hair ring|ring]].

As a [[Magical Girl]] she wears a [[black headwear|black]] [[peaked cap]] with a [[green gemstone]], a [[white collar|white]] [[detached collar]], a [[black necktie|black]] [[cross tie]] with a green [[brooch]], a [[black vest|black]] [[v-neck]] [[vest]] with [[notched lapels]]; [[see-through sleeves|translucent]] [[white sleeves|white]] [[puffy short sleeves]] with [[sleeve cuffs|cuffs]], [[fur cuffs]], a [[black bow|black]] [[waist bow]] with a [[chain]], a [[pleated skirt|pleated]] [[multicolored skirt|multicolored]] [[vertical-striped skirt|vertical-striped]] [[miniskirt]], [[garter straps]], [[black thighhighs|black]] [[fur trim|fur-trimmed]] [[fishnet thighhighs|fishnet]] [[fur-trimmed thighhighs|thighhighs]] and [[black footwear|black]] [[fold-over boots]].

She is voiced by [[Taketatsu Ayana]].

title: civil_war_(stand)
body:
Civil War is the [[Stand (jojo)|]] of [[Axl RO]], featured in the seventh part of the [[JoJo No Kimyou Na Bouken]] series, [[Steel Ball Run]].

Civil War is embodied by a [[humanoid robot|humanoid]] figure. Its head is relatively overwrought, composed of many vertical, elliptical discs pressed together, three of which taper below into arrow shapes; while three objects, resembling those housing the filters in a gas mask, emanate from the base of its neck at its front and sides. The head is designed with the appearance of a distorted metal mask in mind, with it being the focus of the [[Stand (jojo)|]].

A bare spine is visible from its ribcage to its pelvis, and its lower legs are shaped as fraying bell-bottoms. The legs were designed with the picture of plants, giving them a root-like appearance. From the knees to feet of the legs, the color is changed to a maroon, and the steel sticks out at various angles, revealing boots at the bottom.

Civil War generates ghosts of a sort, ranging in type from inanimate objects to humans with varying degrees of constitution and form, which could be considered part of it.

title: paid_reward
body:
[b]Uploading paid rewards is not allowed[/b]. 
See forum #168930 for details.

A paid reward is a paywalled image from Patreon or any other similar site. Sites like these require that the user subscribe or pledge some amount of money every month to view and download these works. 
Alternatively, sites like Gumroad offer archived or other exclusive content, where this tag will also apply. 

Paid rewards include paid content from any of these sites:

* [[Patreon reward]]
* [[Enty reward]]
* [[Fantia reward]]
* [[Fanbox reward]]
* [[Gumroad reward]]

h4. Guidelines

Uploading paid rewards is against the rules. These are the rules for paid rewards:

* Public or free posts aren't paid rewards.
* If a post was free at the time of upload, then it's allowed.
* If an artist releases a paid reward for free later on, then it's allowed.
* Deliberately uploading paid rewards, even with this tag, will result in a warning then a ban.
* Paid rewards uploaded before 2020-07-06 are allowed.
* Paid rewards uploaded after 2020-07-06 should be reported in topic #32324 so they can be banned.
* [b]Be careful about uploading posts from Yande.re, E-Hentai, Kemono.su, or other sites that host unmarked paid rewards. Also be careful when uploading unmarked paid rewards hosted by potential art thieves.[/b]

h4. See also

* [s]topic #10525[/s] topic #32324 - Paid reward ban request topic
* topic #11399
* topic #17033
* topic #17092
* forum #168930 
* [[paid reward available]]

body:

Marisa flies by [[broom riding|riding]] a [[broom]] and fuels her magic with phantasmal [[mushroom]]s, which have given occasion to countless fanon jokes. Uses the [[Master Spark]] move when fighting, which she powers with her favorite artifact, the [[mini-hakkero]].

She has [[long hair|long]] [[blonde hair]] with a [[single braid|single]] [[side braid]] tied with a [[hair bow]]. Her outfit varies, but is usually some variation of a [[black hat|black]] [[witch hat]] with [[frilled hat|frills]], a [[buttons|buttoned]] [[black vest]] over a [[turtleneck shirt|turtleneck]] [[white shirt]] with [[puffy short sleeves]], a [[skirt set|matching]] [[frilled skirt|frilled]] [[black skirt]], a [[frilled apron|frilled]] [[white apron|white]] [[waist apron]], [[white socks]], and either [[black shoes|black]] [[mary janes]] or [[brown footwear|brown]] [[boots]].

h4. Appearance

title: noel_(cookie)
body:
Voice of [[Hakurei Reimu|Reimu]] in [[Atouda Ako (character)|]]'s [[Cookie (Touhou)|Kuso☆]]. The only thing know about her is that she is an artist by profession. Her acting was clear and she had a cute voice, so she maintained a constant level of popularity.

She is strongly associated with [[sumo]] and often holds a [[gunbai]] [[war fan]] and [[enema]], based on the voice drama. Her fearless attitude of organizing laxative sumo match in the video led people to depict her as someone who is so confident in their strength they take their life very easy. She gained more popularity as a main character in [[OFFSide: DIYUSI]] as the [[empty eyes|empty-eyed]] merchant, who knows more than they let on.

h4. Appearance

title: sananana_(cookie)
body:
Voice of [[Hakurei Reimu]] in [[Cookie (Touhou)|Cookie☆☆ S3]] and [[Komeiji Koishi]] in Nabe☆. Drawn with [[short hair|short]] [[black hair]] and [[yellow eyes]]. Very often drawn as a [[magical girl]] wearing a pink version of Reimu's clothes or as an [[office lady]]. Very rarely drawn with [[long hair]] and long [[sidelocks]]. The number 3777 can be shortened to her name, so sometimes appears too.

While initially unpopular, the 2014 boom of the RIM Family of her, [[Benikurage (cookie)|]], [[Kanna (cookie)|]], [[Reu (cookie)|]], and [[Yamin (cookie)|]] gradually increased her standing. This led to her characterization in fan art and media to be almost entirely disconnected from both her appearance in the voice dramas and any information about her real life.

A false rumor of her being 27 years old stuck and led her to being depicted as an embarrassing woman who dresses up in costumes and pretends to be a high-schooler to fit in with the other voice actresses. This was perpetuated by her saying she was "in her 20s" and doing an audio recording of a middle-schooler magical girl/idol. Another copypasta had her sexually attracted to dolphins, particularly [[Kairu the Dolphin]] of [[Microsoft Office]]. Her age also means she is drawn with [[pubic hair]] and [[armpit hair]] which later contributed to [[Shiromiya Rei]]'s association. Also commonly paired with [[Rei (cookie)|]]-kun, as a sort of [[onee-shota]] relationship.

h4. Appearance

* !asset #21018214: Profile (Reimu version)
* !asset #21018215: Profile (Koishi version)

title: kanna_(cookie)
body:
Voice of [[Hakurei Reimu]] in [[cookie_(touhou)|Cookie☆☆ S2]].

Drawn with [[brown hair]] and [[brown eyes|eyes]], with her distinct [b]~[/b] shaped [[blush]]es. Her stated height is 172cm, so she is drawn taller and with [[large breasts|larger breasts]] than the other Reimus. Her angry mother-like voice and attitude also has her appear as the mom figure to [[Yamin (cookie)|]] and [[Benikurage (cookie)|]]. Her voice also has her drawn as the most combative Reimu, with a [[dark persona]] that she fights.

She initially hated the attention that Cookie gave her, especially after her stalker [[Suzuki (cookie)|]] made national headlines when he was arrested for threatening to burn her alive. However, she warmed back up to Cookie after a few years, and has since become an [[Indie virtual youtuber|Indie]] [[virtual youtuber|VTuber]] in a [[miko]] costume.

title: yuyusu_(cookie)
body:
Voice of [[Ibuki Suika]] in [[cookie_(touhou)|Gorgonzola☆]], the artist / [[Hakurei Reimu]] and Sunny Milk (as [[Shiriri Saikyo]]) and Izayoi Sakuya (as [[Ein (cookie)|]]) in [[cookie (touhou)|Self Contradiction☆]], and as Maria in Kussoo☆☆☆☆☆☆. Identifiable by her [[arms up]] pose as Suika, her [[very long hair|very long]] [[gradient hair|gradient]] [[black hair|black]] and [[grey hair]] with [[low twintails]] in a [[sleeveless dress|sleeveless]] [[red dress]] as Reimu. She had a very distinctive high-pitched voice and speech pattern and frequently did live chats with [[Mochiya (cookie)|]] and [[Kinu (cookie)|]]. She was a fairly active artist too, but in January 2020 she said her step-father found out about her voice acting and told her to stop, including her brief stint as the vtuber Kuesu Hatena.

Her most common depictions are her roles in Self-Contradiction☆ but the sub-characters have been split off into their own articles here so this tag is just for her main appearances as Suika and Reimu. Self-Contradiction☆ being a massively important voice drama made her into one of the most popular Cookie voice actors of the later part of the fandom, even if it aired after she disappeared. Most of her appearances in fan art focus on her role as the fame-desperate artist. 

However, people began to suspect she was lying about her step-father telling her to stop. In March 2020, a [[Sugar Lyric]] [[virtual Youtuber|VTuber]] named [[Shishio Chris]] debuted with a suspiciously similar voice, a love of twitcasting, lots of merch of Yokohama DeNA Baystars, and a familiarity with VTubing. Within 2 days Cookie fans had all but confirmed that it was her.

h4. Appearance

* !asset #21104606: Profile (1)
* !asset #21104607: Profile (2)

body:
Voice of [[Hakurei Reimu]] in [[cookie_(touhou)|Cookie☆☆ S1]]. Has [[brown hair]] and [[brown eyes]] with a noticeable [[parted bangs|center part]]. Mostly seen with her [[orange scarf|orange]] and [[red scarf|red]] [[striped scarf]] and [[red mittens]]. In real life she has [[long hair|long]] [[black hair]]. Is probably [[Kakinota Neina]] too.

Since mentioning in some of her streams that her father tried to put a stray [[cat]] as part of nabe and that she burned the Quran (if these statements are true is unknown), fans have associated her with cats and Islamism. She has has a minor running joke of having a coating on her tongue.

title: ghostly_mita_(miside)
body:
Ghostly Mita, formerly known as Emotional Mita, is a character from [[MiSide]]. She is a young woman that initially appears as a dark silhouette, devoid of any color.

After helping her, she regains most of herself, with the exception of [[faceless|her face]], which was stolen by [[Crazy Mita (Miside)|Crazy Mita]].

Like most other Mitas, Ghostly Mita is a young woman of average height with [[medium breasts]], [[purple hair]]. 

Her clothing is identical to default Mitas - she wears [[red thighhighs]], a [[blue_skirt|blue]], [[pleated_skirt|pleated]] skirt, a [[red shirt]], a [[red choker]] and a red [[hairclip]].

Her distinctive features include her [[long hair|long]] [[purple hair]] styled into a [[ponytail]], her aforementioned lack of a face.

title: mash_kyrielight
body:
[b]Mash Kyrielight[/b] (マシュ・キリエライト; also romanized as Matthew or Mashu) is a female character from [[Fate/Grand Order]] of the Shielder class. She is a Demi-Servant, a human fused with a Heroic Spirit. She works at the Chaldea Security Organization.

She is the first person [[Fujimaru Ritsuka|the protagonist]] sees when he/she wakes up in Chaldea. She has [[short hair|short]], [[purple hair]] which [[hair over one eye|covers her right eye]] and [[purple eyes]]. When not in her servant form, she wears a [[necktie]], [[black dress]], [[jacket]], [[black pantyhose]] and [[glasses]]. In her servant form, she wears an [[armored dress]] and carries an enormous [[shield]], Lord Chaldeas (named by [[Olga Marie Animusphere]]). Later in the story it is revealed that [spoiler]the shield is in fact [[Lord Camelot (fate)|]], [[Galahad_(Fate)|Galahad's]] Noble Phantasm.[/spoiler]

[b]Character Design:[/b] [[Takeuchi Takashi]]
[b]Voice Actress:[/b] [[Taneda Risa]] (before Sep 2016), [[Takahashi Rie]] (current)

title: tsukishiro_yuki
body:
A [[spoilers|spoiler]] character of [[Mahou Shoujo no Majo Saiban]].

[spoilers]The former classmate of [[Sakuraba Ema]] and [[Nikaidou Hiro]] thought to be dead. She is revealed to be the last surviving "Great Witch" and the true mastermind behind the prison that the girls are trapped in.

Before she met Ema and Hiro while disguised as a human, she took in [[Hikami Meruru]] during her time as a witch, and considered her as family.

She has [[white hair]] and [[white eyes]], and usually dresses in a [[white dress|white]] [[lolita fashion|lolita]] dress.[/spoilers]

title: alice_margatroid
body:
The "Seven-Colored Puppeteer".

[[Touhou]] character. Stage 3 and Extra Stage boss of [[Mystic Square]] and later a recurring playable character. One of the few [[touhou (pc-98)|PC-98 era]] characters (along with [[Hakurei Reimu|Reimu]] and [[Kirisame Marisa|Marisa]]) to reappear in the Windows-era games. She first appeared in her current design as the Stage 3 boss of [[Perfect Cherry Blossom]]. She is often accompanied by her dolls, [[Shanghai Doll]], [[Hourai Doll]], or [[Goliath Doll]].

A human-turned-youkai [[witch]] who specializes in manipulating [[doll]]s and using them to attack her enemies. Unlike [[Kirisame Marisa|Marisa]], her neighbor in the [[Forest of Magic]], Alice is not only rather aloof, but also somewhat cowardly at heart, refusing to use her full power for any reason because she would not know how to deal with losing. This nature leads to [[doujinshi]] portraying her as having some tendencies of being [[tsundere]] towards her [[human village (touhou)|human neighbor]]. Speculated to be the daughter of [[Shinki (touhou)|]]. Bearer of the [[Grimoire of Alice]].

She has [[short hair|short]] [[blonde hair]] with a [[frilled hairband|frilled]] [[red hairband]] and [[blue eyes]]. Her outfit is a [[pink neckerchief|pink]] or [[red neckerchief]], a [[white capelet]] over a (possibly) [[sleeveless dress|sleeveless]] [[blue dress]] and a [[long sleeves|long-sleeved]] [[white shirt]], a [[pink sash|pink]] or [[red sash]], and [[brown boots]].

h4. Appearance

title: junko_(touhou)
body:
[i][[Touhou]][/i] character introduced as the final boss in [i][[Legacy of Lunatic Kingdom]][/i]. A divine spirit with the power to purify anything. 

She has [[long hair|long]] [[blonde hair|blonde]] or [[orange hair]] and [[red eyes]]. She wears a [[dalachi (headdress)|]] with a [[crescent]] moon on it and [[Chinese clothes]] with a [[red tabard]]. Behind her are [[multiple tails|multiple]] [[fox tail|fox tails]] made out of energy.

She is the embodiment of all hatred against the Lunarian race, especially [[Chang'e (touhou)|]], whose husband shot down the sun and killed Junko's son [[Bofeng]]. She is friends with [[Hecatia Lapislazuli]] who sympathized with her as she holds a grudge against Chang'e as well.

Unlike other Touhou characters, she has no in-game title. Her official profile simply says "(無名の存在)"/"(Nameless Being)" in place of a title, likely because she has purified herself of all identifying information.

h4. Appearance

* !post #2097432: Profile

title: bofeng
body: [[junko_(touhou)|Junko's]] deceased son and reason for her grudge against [[Chang'e (touhou)|]]. His appearance is unknown but he is often represented with an appearance similar to his mother's, including a decorated [[red tabard]], Chinese noble hat and clothes in black, and [[blonde hair]].

title: hou_yi_(touhou)
body: Houyi was [[Chang'e (touhou)|]]'s husband, and also the one who killed Junko's son and shot down the suns, creating [[Junko (touhou)|]] and [[Hecatia Lapislazuli]]'s grudge. He was eventually killed by Junko. In [[Touhou]], it is unknown which version of him exists: in one story, he is a loving husband who becomes helpless as Chang'e is forced to drink the elixir; in another, he is a despotic ruler who Chang'e is forced to stop by consuming the elixir in his place; in yet another, it is Chang'e who gives in to the elixir's temptation. They are sometimes known to represent the yin and yang.

title: hecatia_lapislazuli
body:
[[Touhou]] character.

Based on the Greek goddess [[Hecate (mythology)|]], Hecatia is a goddess who governs the Hells of the Earth, Moons and Otherworlds.  Like [[Junko (Touhou)|]], she also has a grudge against Chang'e, whose husband shot down Apollo and indirectly weakened Hell, as Hell wouldn't be able to exist without the sun. She's friends with Junko, and lent her [[Clownpiece]], her subordinate, to fulfill her plans.

She has [[red hair]], [[red eyes]] and wears a [[black shirt|black]] [[off-shoulder shirt|off-shoulder]] [[t-shirt]] (that is sometimes depicted as a [[crop top]]) along with a [[multicolored skirt|tri-colored]] [[plaid skirt]] of [[green skirt|green]], [[red skirt|red]], and [[blue skirt|blue]], and a [[black hat]]. She also carries ornaments of [[Moon (ornament)| the moon]], [[Earth (ornament)| the Earth]], and [[underworld (ornament)|the Spirit World]] with her, representing her ability to exist in 3 locations at once. Her hair and eye color change according to the ornament she wears in her hat: red when it's the Spirit World, [[blue hair|blue]] when it's [[Hecatia Lapislazuli (Earth)|Earth]], and [[blonde hair|blonde]] when it's the [[Hecatia Lapislazuli (Moon)|moon]], although it's not uncommon to see her with "other objects on her head.":/pools/10382

Her fashion sense has earned her the nickname "Hot Topic-chan":/pools/10945 among fans.

title: chess_piece
body:
Any of the various pieces or "men" used to play [[chess]].

h4. Types

* [[rook (chess)]]
* [[knight (chess)]]
* [[bishop (chess)]]
* [[queen (chess)]]
* [[king (chess)]]

title: pawn_(chess)
body: A [[chess piece]] with a bead on top, meant to represent the pawn in the game of chess. Normally a pawn moves by advancing a single square, but the first time a pawn is moved, it has the option of advancing two squares.

title: knight_(chess)
body: A [[chess piece]] shaped like a [[horse]]'s head, meant to represent the knight in the game of chess. The knight moves on an extended diagonal from one corner of any 2×3 rectangle of squares to the furthest opposite corner. Consequently, the knight alternates its square color each time it moves.

title: bishop_(chess)
body: A [[chess piece]] with the design of an abbot's [[mitre]], meant to represent the bishop in the game of chess. The bishop has no restrictions in distance for each move, but is limited to diagonal movement.

title: queen_(chess)
body: A [[chess piece]] with a spiked crown design, meant to represent the queen in the game of chess. The queen is the most powerful piece in the game of chess, able to move any number of squares vertically, horizontally or diagonally. Each player starts the game with one queen, placed in the middle of the first rank next to the king.

title: rook_(chess)
body: A [[chess piece]] with the design of a siege tower, meant to represent the rook, formerly called the castle, in the game of chess. The rook moves horizontally or vertically, through any number of unoccupied squares.

title: king_(chess)
body: A [[chess piece]] with a crown that has a cross on top, meant to represent the king in the game of chess. The objective in chess is to capture the opponent's king piece in a move called checkmate. Although the king is the most important piece, it is usually the weakest piece in the game until a later phase, the endgame. Players cannot make any move that places their own king in check.

title: flandre_scarlet
body:
A [[Touhou]] character (alt. spelling Frandre, Flandoll, Frandoll). The "Diabolic Wave". Extra Stage boss of [[Touhou]]'s [[Embodiment of Scarlet Devil]] and Playable Character in [[Sunken Fossil World]].

The younger, mentally unstable sister of [[Remilia Scarlet]], sealed in the basement of the [[Scarlet Devil Mansion]] for 495 years because of her ability to cause wanton destruction. Despite her sheltered life, she is fond of her sister, usually never tries to leave the mansion, and in more recent works such as [[Foul Detective Satori]] has shown a remarkable growth in stability and self-awareness. Flandre is easily distinguished by her unique, [[multicolored wings|multicolored]] [[crystal wings]].

Sometimes drawn with her weapon, [[Laevatein (touhou)|]]. Alternatively, it might be depicted as a tail; see [[laevatein (tail)]].

title: hua_cheng
body:
[b]Hua Cheng[/b] is the deuteragonist of [[Tianguan Cifu|Heaven Official's Blessing]]. He is a ghost of Supreme rank and the Husband of [[Xie Lian]].

He has a single [[side braid]] with [[hair beads]]. He wears an [[eyepatch]] and dressed in [[red hanfu]] with a [[butterfly necklace|butterfly]] shaped [[silver necklace]], along with [[silver bracelet]] and [[silver belt]]. title: ironmouse
body:
[[Demon girl]] [[indie virtual youtuber|indie]] [[virtual youtuber|VTuber]]. One of the founding members of [[VShojo]], she operated under them from November 2020 to July 2025, where she would leave the agency "while accusing them of owing over $500,000 to charity":[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MwLbGcUMy6g]. She originally debuted using a "free FaceRig model":[https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=1106528883] of [[Touhoku Kiritan]] in 2017 (now known as Season 0), before debuting her demon girl self in 2019. Has a genetically caused "immunodeficiency":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Common_variable_immunodeficiency]. She also played as a member of [[Quackity SMP]].

She has [[demon wings]], [[demon horns|horns]] and a [[demon tail]], with [[purple eyes]] (although in some costumes, she gains [[heterochromia]] with her left eye becoming [[red eyes|red]]). For her regular hairstyle, she has her [[long hair|long]] [[pink hair|pink]] with [[purple hair|purple]] [[streaked hair|streaks]] done in a [[two side up]].

title: sitting
body:
The butt resting on a surface (often a [[chair]], [[couch]], or [[bench]]), possibly in addition to the legs or feet. For a position with the knees on the floor, use [[kneeling]] (except with seiza below).

h4. Examples

* !post #3279793: (left to right: [[yokozuwari]], [[butterfly sitting]], [[wariza]], [[hugging own legs]])
* !post #2866134: (left to right: [[indian style]], [[seiza]], [[knees up]], [[wariza]], [i]hidden[/i], [[crossed ankles]])

h4. Related tags

h6. Positions

* [[Butterfly sitting]]: Rump on floor, knees splayed, soles of feet joined together.
* [[Crossed legs]]: Rump on chair, one leg on top of the other at the knee.
* [[Figure four sitting]]: in a chair, the ankle or calf of one leg resting on the knee of the other.
* [[Indian style]]: Rump on floor, legs crossed at the ankles like a pretzel.
* [[Lotus position]]: like Indian style, but with feet placed on opposite thighs with soles facing upward and heels close to the abdomen.
* [[Seiza]]: Rump on legs, both legs below body.
* [[Sitting backwards]]: in a chair, facing the backrest.
* [[Sitting sideways]]: in a chair, facing the side.
* [[Wariza]]: Rump on floor, legs bent back on either side.
* [[Yokozuwari]]: Rump on floor, legs both to the same side.

title: raspberry_mousse_cookie
body:
A character from [[Cookie Run]]. 

He debuted in [[Cookie Run: OvenBreak|OvenBreak]] on January 30th, 2020.

In [[Cookie Run: OvenBreak|OvenBreak]], his combi pet is [[Poodleberry]].

He is the cousin of [[Raspberry Cookie]].

title: galea_(xenoblade)
body:
[[Xenoblade Chronicles (series)|]] character.

[spoiler]A human scientist in the events before [[Xenoblade Chronicles (series)|]]. Colleague of [[Klaus (xenoblade)|]]. Through the Phase Transition Experiment, she became the goddess [[Meyneth (xenoblade)|]].
other_names: ガラテア(ゼノブレイド)

title: klaus_(xenoblade)
body:
[[Xenoblade Chronicles (series)|]] character.

[spoiler]A human scientist in the events before [[Xenoblade Chronicles (series)|]]. Colleague of [[Galea (xenoblade)|]]. Through the Phase Transition Experiment, half of him was sent to another universe to become [[Zanza (xenoblade)|]], god of the [[Bionis]], while the rest of him remained to become the [[Architect (xenoblade)|]] of Alrest.
other_names: クラウス(ゼノブレイド)

title: master_crown
body:
An ancient artifact in the [i][[Kirby (series)|]][/i] games, introduced in [i][[Kirby's Return to Dream Land]][/i]. It is said to give its wearer unlimited power.

[spoiler]The main story of [i]Kirby's Return to Dream Land[/i] is driven by [[Magolor]]'s efforts to steal the Crown from its current guardian, [[Landia]]. After enlisting the help of [[Kirby]] [[king_dedede|and]] [[meta_knight|his]] [[bandana_waddle_dee|friends]], he succeeds in doing so and attempts to conquer the universe, starting with [[Planet Popstar]]. The Crown's influence and evil sentience get the better of him and he transforms into a [[magolor_soul|monster]] that is swiftly defeated by Kirby and company.[/spoiler]

[spoiler][[Void Termina]] is able to summon the Crown (or at least a replica of it) during his boss battle in [i][[Kirby Star Allies]][/i]. This along with the Jambastion sigil closely resembling the Crown suggests a strong connection with him, [[Dark Matter (kirby)|]], and the twisted treasure.[/spoiler]

[spoiler][i][[Kirby's Return to Dream Land Deluxe]][/i] confirms that the Master Crown is in fact, sentient, having brought the downfall of multiple civilizations in the past. In the [i][[Magolor Epilogue]][/i], it first enhances the [[Grand Doomer]] into the [[Crowned Doomer]], then assimilates the [[Gem Apple]] to turn into [[master crown (tree)|a tree monster]] before being poetically struck down by Magolor’s [[Ultra Sword]].[/spoiler]

title: crowned_doomer
body: The [[Grand Doomer]] empowered by the fragments of the [[Master Crown]], serving as the penultimate boss of [[Magolor Epilogue]].

title: greater_doomer
body: A purple-colored [[Doomer (Kirby)|]] seen in [[Team Kirby Clash Deluxe]] and [[Super Kirby Clash]]. As indicated by the number of [[feathers]] on its underside, it is in-between the [[Sphere Doomer]]s and [[Grand Doomer]] in power.

title: torogao
body:
A facial expression where the character appears to be in an ecstatic, yet quiet and unresponsive state of pleasure.

The cheeks look [[blush|flushed]], the eyebrows are slanted downwards towards the sides, and the eyes are half-open and [[tears|moist]], often staring into the distance. It is common to see [[saliva]] and a half-[[open mouth]] as well. The limbs and joints may be relaxed and hanging loosely in place. May also involve [[heavy breathing]] or a contented [[smile]].

It is often sexual in nature, but not always. It may also be seen when a character is eating their favorite food, for example. 

Not to be confused with [[ahegao]], which is a more exaggerated expression. Torogao indicates trance-like pleasure.

h4. Examples

* !post #531234
* !post #4933778

h4. See also

* [[ahegao]]
* [[fucked silly]]
* [[Tag Group:Face Tags]]

title: in_water
body:
Ambiguous tag. Use one of the following instead:

h5. Objects
* [[Immersed]] - When an object is completely under.
* [[Partially immersed]] - When an object is at the surface.

h5. People
* [[Submerged]] - When a person is completely under.
* [[Partially submerged]] - A person standing, sitting or lying in water more than waist deep.
* [[Wading]] - A person standing in water less than waist deep.
* [[Soaking feet]] - A person sitting near a body of water with up to their lower legs submerged.

h5. Perspective
* [[Partially underwater shot]] - When the perspective, i.e. "camera" of the image is partially submerged.
* [[Underwater]] - When the entire setting is under.

title: ragdoll
body:
A rag doll is a doll, usually made from scraps of fabric, often soft and flexible. It is a doll (a popular toy worldwide) made of fabric, traditionally homemade from rag scraps and stuffed with scraps of material, often soft and flexible.

This tag can be used regardless of whether it is an object or a character that is a rag doll itself.

title: alex_danvers
body:
[b]Alex Danvers[/b] (Full name: Alexandra Danvers) is a character from the CW Network's [[Supergirl (2015)|]] TV series.

She is the older adopted sister of Kara Danvers/[[Supergirl]], who was adopted by the Danvers family after Kara's escape pod landed on Earth years after the destruction of the planet Krypton and was found by her cousin [[Superman]], who handed Kara to the Danvers for safety.

In the show, Alex is an agent of the Department of Extranormal Operations (DEO), a secret government agency tasked with monitoring alien presence on Earth. Despite not being related by blood, both Alex and Kara cared for each other whenever they're in trouble. In season 2, Alex comes out as a Lesbian, who kept her sexuality a secret due to past trauma as a teenager due to being rejected by a girl she had a crush on.

title: sagiri_(swimsuit)_(kancolle)
body:
The [[swimsuit]] [[official alternate costume]] of [[Kantai Collection]]'s [[Sagiri (kancolle)|]]. 

She wears a [[white one-piece swimsuit|white]] [[frilled_swimsuit|frilled]] [[casual_one-piece_swimsuit|casual one-piece]] [[highleg one-piece swimsuit|highleg swimsuit]] with a [[criss-cross halter]], [[side-tie_swimsuit|tied on the sides]] and held with small [[anchor]]s, initially under a frilled turtleneck side-tie shirt which disappears in Kai form. Optional are a [[white choker]], a [[hairband]] [[hair_flower|adorned with white flowers]], a pair of [[earrings]] apparently shaped like [[lemon slice]]s, a long [[white shawl]], and [[sandals]]. The apparent skimpiness of the swimsuit and its elegant design, especially the Kai form, have in some way provided a minor popularity boost to one of the more forgotten Ayanami sisters.

Also became a [[sagiri_(kancolle)_(cosplay)|popular cosplay item]] upon implementation, thus giving it the [i]rei no mizugi[/i] (例の水着; i.e. "[i]that[/i] swimsuit") tag.

* !post #5505179: Kai

title: emmet_(pokemon)
body:
[b]Emmet[/b], known as [b]Kudari[/b] (クダリ) in Japan, is a character introduced in [i][[pokemon|Pokémon]] [[pokemon bw|Black and White]][/i].

This Subway Boss is the younger of the twin brothers who run the Battle Subway in Unova. He likes working with different combinations of Pokémon in Double Battles [tn](official bio)[/tn]. 

He has [[grey eyes]] and [[short hair|short]] [[grey hair]] with [[sidelocks]] (could be depicted as [[long sideburns]] in some drawings). He wears a [[white headwear|white]] [[peaked cap|cap]], a [[long sleeves|long-sleeve]] [[high collar]] [[white coat|white]] [[trench coat|coat]], a [[collared shirt|collared]] [[white shirt|white]] [[dress shirt|shirt]] with a [[blue necktie|tie]], [[white gloves|gloves]], a [[belt buckle|buckled]] [[brown belt|belt]], and [[white pants]] and  [[white shoes]].

title: ingo_(pokemon)

This Subway Boss is the older of the twin brothers who run the Battle Subway in Unova. He usually specializes in Single Battles [tn](official bio)[/tn].

[b]The Moon Princess Possessed by Divine Spirits[/b]

A [[Touhou]] character introduced in the manga [i][[Silent Sinner in Blue]][/i]. A Lunarian princess and younger sister of [[Watatsuki no Toyohime]]. She has the ability to summon the powers of Shinto gods, similar to [[Hakurei Reimu]], but is more skilled at it due to superior experience and training.

Yorihime wears her [[purple hair]] in a [[ponytail]] with a [[yellow ribbon]]. Her [[red dress]] has a [[single strap]] and she often wields a [[katana]]. 

Bears a striking resemblance to [[Meira (Touhou)|Meira]], and later, [[Komakusa Sannyo]].

title: kisaki_(blue_archive)
body:
A character from [[Blue Archive]]. The president of the Xuanlong Office and the student council president of the Shanhaijing Secondary School. Her full name is Ryuuge Kisaki.

She has a dragon-shaped [[halo]], [[long hair|long]] [[black hair]] and [[grey eyes]]. Her regular hairstyle consists of [[double bun]]s with a [[bun with braided base|braided base]] that turn into [[twintails]] held with [[butterfly hair ornament]]s. Her outfit consists of a [[short dress|short]] [[black dress|black]] [[sleeveless dress|sleeveless]] [[china dress]] with a [[back cutout]], a [[side slit]] a [[pelvic curtain]] and a [[dragon print|dragon]] [[print dress|print]], a [[grey coat|grey]] [[vertical-striped coat]] with [[pinstripe pattern]], [[black gloves|black]] [[half gloves]] and [[black shoes|black]] [[pumps]].

She's often drawn with her [[arms up]], performing the "Banzai stretch", which originated from episode 3 of the in-game event "Catch in Neverland":[https://bluearchive.fandom.com/wiki/Catch_in_Neverland].

Her weapon is based on the [[CS/LS06]] [[submachine gun]].

title: fossilized_wonders
body:
(Touhou Kinjoukyou) 〜 Fossilized Wonders
("Crowning Glory Capital") 

20th mainline game of the [[Touhou]] series. It was announced on April 12, 2025. However, the game immediately gained controversy after the demo’s release for using [[AI-generated background]]s, together with a concurrent music takedown. Interestingly enough, the game's plot revolves around AI, with the final boss even having "AI" as her initials (in the Western naming order).

The trial released on May 5, 2025, with the full version being out on August 17, 2025.

title: rezi
body:
Artist, digital colorist for visual novels and illustrations.

Has worked in VN studio "Witch":[https://vndb.org/p768] between 1999 and 2005 as CG chief and CG supervision, in VN studio "Miris Pellet":[https://vndb.org/p1533] as CG chief ([[Tutorial Summer]], 2005) and between 2005 and 2018 in VN studio "AXL":[https://vndb.org/p214] as CG chief, all under pseudonym "tetu". He's friends with [[Senomoto Hisashi]] (character designer, artist, founder of AXL). Worked on some graphics (backgrounds and effects) in [[Sorcery Jokers]] VN (2015, available in English). Worked on "Gensou Rougoku no Kaleidoscope (2020)":[https://vndb.org/v25583#main] backgrounds and chibi (SD) characters coloring.

His illustrations were featured in the artbook "100 Masters of Bishoujo Paintings generation 2":[https://www.amazon.co.jp/%E7%B5%B5%E5%B8%AB100%E4%BA%BA-generation2-%E6%9D%91%E7%94%B0%E8%93%AE%E7%88%BE/dp/4861008883] (絵師100人 generation2, 2013). Were also displayed in "pixiv × FIREFLY Illustration Exhibition":[https://times.pixiv.net/post/119270687085/pixivxfirefly] in Guangzhou, China in 2015.

He's been doing coloring for Senomoto Hisashi's doujinshi covers ("Million Bank":[https://www.doujinshi.org/browse/circle/1511/Million-Bank/]) and some monochrome drawings on the last pages. Also drawn covers for Angel's Stroke issue 18 and 28. Has never made any doujinshi or manga.

Has done character designs for Isabella in [[Hortensia Saga]] mobile game (from f4samurai), Miharu Katagiri in [[Shooting Girl]] browser game (from DMM) and for 5 playable girls in [[monster_hunter_mezeporta_kaitaku-ki|Monster Hunter Mezeporta Reclamation]] browser game (from DMM).

Over the years he deleted or set to private many works on his Pixiv account, but thanks to uploaders they are available on gelbooru, danbooru, sankaku and other websites.

title: watatsuki_no_toyohime
body:
[b]The Moon Princess Connecting Sea and Mountain[/b]
[b][spoiler]The Sage Who Links the Triangular Mountain and the Sea   (Fossilized Wonders)[/spoiler][/b]

A [[Touhou]] character introduced in the manga [[Silent Sinner in Blue]]. Lunarian princess and older sister of [[Watatsuki no Yorihime]]. She has the ability to manipulate boundaries, similar to [[Yakumo Yukari]], but her power is limited to boundaries involving the moon. She has a [[folding_fan|fan]] capable of mass destruction (said to be big enough to wipe out the Bamboo Forest completely).

Toyohime has [[blonde hair]] with [[yellow eyes]]. Her [[hat]] has a [[purple bow]], and her [[purple dress]] has a [[single strap]].

[spoiler]She makes her first appearance in a mainline game as the Stage 5 Boss of [[Fossilized Wonders]], where she received a slight redesign: Her hat is now a [[mob cap]] with a [[purple ribbon]], her fan and her eyes are now [[red_eyes|red]]. [/spoiler]

[spoiler]In FW, Toyohime is revealed to be the administrator of the Asama Impurity-Cleansing Mountain, a Lunarian facility in Gensokyo. In order to prevent the influx of impurity from destroying the Lunar Capital, she unsealed Ariya and rebooted Yuiman to resolve the incident on the Lunar Capital, leading to time being frozen in Gensokyo and creating a new incident.[/spoiler]

[spoiler]Similar to Sagume, Toyohime is one of the few non final boss characters in the series to not have a "defeated" portrait.[/spoiler]

h4. Appearance

* !post #175298
* !post #9811567

h4. External links

* "Touhou wiki: Watatsuki no Toyohime":https://en.touhouwiki.net/wiki/Watatsuki_no_Toyohime

title: michigami_nareko
body:
[b]Confined Dousojin of Hallowed Ground[/b]

Stage 3 Boss of [[Fossilized Wonders]]. The "Dōsojin of the Enclosed Sanctuary". 

Nareko is a Dousojin who guards the entrance to the pyramidal altar underneath Youkai Mountain, preventing people from coming in and out of the pyramid. She is not Egyptian, but is inspired by the Sphinx to challenge visitors with riddles, manipulating the answers to give herself an advantage. [spoiler]One of Marisa's endings reveals that she was created and placed by Chimi at the altar a long time ago.[/spoiler] 

Has [[blue eyes]], [[triangle facial mark]], [[key earrings]] and [[low-tied long hair|low-tied]] [[long hair|long]] [[blue hair]] with [[blunt bangs]] and [[quad tails]] bound in a [[gold jewelry|gold]] [[headpiece]]. Wears a [[yellow capelet|gold]] and [[blue capelet|blue]] [[striped capelet|striped]] [[capelet]], [[brown shirt|brown]] [[short sleeves|short sleeved]] shirt, [[brown shorts]] with a [[belt]], [[brown boots]] and [[black thighhighs]]. Wields a golden [[staff]] and [[scepter]].

h4. Appearance

* !post #9257317

h4. External links

* "Touhou Wiki: Michigami Nareko":https://en.touhouwiki.net/wiki/Nareko_Michigami

title: houjuu_chimi
body:
[b]Unidentified Unruly Beast[/b]

Stage 2 Boss of [[Fossilized Wonders]]. An outsider who can only live in places with a lot of nature, like mountains, forests and rivers. As her name suggests, she is a Chimimouryou, and her species predates the modern concept of Youkai. [spoiler]One of Marisa's endings reveals that she created Nareko.[/spoiler]

She is [[barefoot]], wears a [[blue dress]], and has [[grey eyes]] alongside her [[white hair]]. A red [[facial mark]] adorns her forehead.

Though she shares a family name with [[Houjuu Nue]], (even having the same kanji - for comparison, [[Kishin Sagume]] and [[Kijin Seija]] do not) any direct relationship between the two is unknown.


h4. Appearance

title: kochiya_sanae
body:
The "Human of the Worshipped Wind". Stage 5 boss of [[Touhou]]'s [[Mountain of Faith]] and later a recurring playable character. Has the power to create miracles.

She is the miko of the [[Moriya Shrine]] under the patronage of [[Yasaka Kanako]] and also direct descendant of the shrine's original deity, [[Moriya Suwako]]. Sanae and her deities moved into [[Gensokyo]] due to waning faith of humans from the outside world, making her one of the only humans from the 21st century. Recent games in the main series as well as certain side works consider her a type of deity in her own right.

She has [[long hair|long]] [[green hair]], with a [[single sidelock]]. Her eyes are [[green eyes|green]] or [[blue eyes|blue]]. In her hair are [[snake hair ornament|snake]] and [[frog hair ornament]]s and a [[single hair tube]]. She is frequently depicted with [[large breasts]]. She wears a [[nontraditional miko]] outfit consisting of a [[sleeveless shirt|sleeveless]] [[collared shirt|collared]] [[white shirt]] (that is sometimes depicted as a [[crop top]]) with [[detached sleeves|detached]] [[white sleeves]], a [[long skirt|long]] [[frilled skirt|frilled]] [[blue skirt]], [[white socks]], and [[brown footwear|brown]] [[shoes]], her signature [[gohei]] is different from the norm as it has straight paper decorations. As of [[Unfinished Dream of All Living Ghost]], she is additionally shown with [[wings]]. Doujins sometimes portray her wearing a modern [[school uniform]] as homage to her origins.

She is a generally good, if somewhat naive and clumsy, girl, but also an "overeager youkai hunter":/pool/show/4639 (leading to her portrayal of frequently bullying [[Tatara Kogasa]] after a scene in [[Undefined Fantastic Object]] where Sanae gave scathing words against the latter).

She is occasionally depicted as a [[retro games sanae (meme)|generation behind]] due to [[Mountain of Faith]] first releasing in 2007.

She is sometimes called "[[player 2|2P]] [[Hakurei Reimu|Reimu]]" or "[[Miko]] [[Luigi]]" due to Reimu's red outfit compared to Sanae's green outfit.

h4. Appearance

* !post #9193946: Profile
* !post #6586874: [[Unfinished Dream of All Living Ghost]]

h4. See also

* [[Retro games Sanae (meme)|]]
* Pool #4639 - For depictions of Sanae in her Youkai Extermination Mode

h4. External links

* "Touhou Wiki: Sanae Kochiya":https://en.touhouwiki.net/wiki/Sanae_Kochiya

title: rayadillo
body:
Rayadillo (transl. striped material) is a blue-and-white striped cotton or flannel material that was used to make the military uniforms worn by Spanish colonial soldiers from the later 19th century until the early 20th century. It was commonly worn by soldiers posted in overseas Spanish tropical colonies, Spanish Morocco and Spanish Guinea, before being adopted as a summer uniform by units stationed in Spain itself.

The Revolutionary Army of the First Philippine Republic under Emilio Aguinaldo also employed the same fabric in their military uniforms during the later years of the Philippine Revolution and the Philippine–American War.

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: Rayadillo":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rayadillo]

title: foreshortening
body:
A technique in which an object is depicted at an angle, making it appear shorter than its actual size. This captures the distortion seen by the eye when viewing an object at an unusual angle.

Not to be confused with [[depth of field]], which refers to blurry, out-of-focus portions of an image. An image can contain both, but not necessarily.

Resembles her sire, [[Mejiro McQueen (racehorse)|]]. Point Flag has a white mane and a white "grey" coat with a grey muzzle and speckled grey spots on her flanks.

title: project_sekai
body:
A mobile rhythm game featuring the [[Piapro studio|Piapro]] family and other original characters. Developed by [[Colorful Palette]]. 

It has two commissioned theme songs for its launch, [[Sekai (vocaloid)|]] and [[Wah Wah World (vocaloid)|]].

About two songs are commissioned each month from known [[Vocaloid]] producers.

title: oyama_mahiro
body:
Protagonist of [[Onii-chan wa Oshimai!]]. He wakes up one morning to find he was [[genderswap_(mtf)|transformed into a girl]] when his little sister [[Oyama Mihari|Mihari]] drugged him the night before.

Only add the [[genderswap (mtf)]] tag if her male form is also present. In situations where she appears alongside her [[Oyama Mahiro (male)|original male]] self, the [[dual persona]] tag should be used.

title: wriggle_nightbug
body:
The "Bug of Light Wriggling in the Dark". Stage 1 boss of [[Touhou]]'s [i][[Imperishable Night]][/i].
A youkai insect (in her case, based on a [[firefly]]) with the ability to manipulate insects. She is best known, however, for the confusion surrounding her gender (due to her [[androgynous]] appearance) prior to the full release of IN. Doujins portray her as a member of [[Team 9 (touhou)|]], a posse of low-tier Touhou characters alongside [[Cirno]], [[Mystia Lorelei]] and [[Rumia]]. Also humorously called "G" (short for "gokiburi", Japanese for "cockroach"), due to the antennae on her head. She is also frequently associated with [[Kazami Yuuka]], because they have similar hairstyles and because bugs pollinate flowers.

She has [[short hair|short]] [[green hair]] and [[green eyes]] with thin [[antennae]] on her head. Her outfit is a [[collared shirt|collared]] [[white shirt]] with [[long sleeves]], a [[two-sided cape|two-sided]] [[black cape|black]] and [[red cape]], [[blue shorts|blue]] or [[black shorts]], [[white socks]], and either [[red shoes|red]] [[mary janes]] or [[brown footwear|brown]] [[loafers]]. 

h4. Appearance

* !asset #23345172: Profile

h4. See also

* [[Princess Wriggle]], a more "feminine" variant

h4. External links

* "Touhou Wiki: Wriggle Nightbug":http://en.touhouwiki.net/wiki/Wriggle_Nightbug

title: elis_(touhou)
body:
A [[Touhou (PC-98)|Touhou PC-98]] character. Makai route Stage 15 boss in [[Highly Responsive to Prayers]].

She has [[purple eyes]], [[blonde hair]] with a large [[red bow|red]] [[hair bow]], and a [[star wand]] in her left hand. She wears a [[white shirt]] with a [[red bowtie]] under her [[purple vest]] and a [[long skirt|long]] [[red skirt]]. She also has [[pointy ears]], and [[facial mark|a red star mark on her face]]. Additionally, she has large, purple [[bat wings]] and has the ability to turn herself into a [[bat (animal)|]].

title: nhk_ni_youkoso!
body:
"NHKにようこそ!  ([i]NHK ni youkoso![/i], Welcome to the NHK)" is a Japanese novel written by Takimoto Tatsuhiko and illustrated by [[Abe Yoshitoshi]]. It dealt with [[hikikomori]]. The manga iteration is illustrated by [[Ooiwa Kenji]].

"NHK" in the title is not "[[nhk (broadcaster)|Nippon Housou Kyoukai]]", the television broadcaster that served as the central plot point in the original novel, but "[b]N[/b]ihon [b]H[/b]ikikomori [b]K[/b]youkai" (lit. "Japanese Anti-Social Corporation"). 

It was adapted into TV anime series and a manga series. Its anime title was altered to "N・H・Kにようこそ! (Welcome to the N.H.K.)" in consideration of [[NHK (broadcaster)|]].

h4.Characters

* [[Satou Tatsuhiro]]

Japanese racehorse. Sired by [[Caerleon (racehorse)|]] and foaled by [[Aghsan (racehorse)|]].

While she is individually famous for winning the 1995 Hanshin Sansai Himba Stakes (Now called the Hanshin Juvenile Fillies), she is most famous for being the mother of [[Buena Vista (racehorse)|]]. Another of her children is [[Admire Japan (racehorse)|]], famous for being a direct rival to [[Deep Impact (racehorse)|]] but now better known for using a beanbag for a pillow.

title: instant_ramen
body:
A form of ramen sold in a dry, precooked block, the most common form of "instant noodles". Invented in Japan in 1958 by [[Nissin]], it has since spread to other countries, examples include America's "Top Ramen" and Britain's "Super Noodles".

The [[instant noodle block]] is generally sold in two sorts of packaging, [[pack noodles]] (generally in square packs, sometimes sold in bulk) or [[cup ramen]] (generally sold in a cup- or bowl-shaped container).

title: yellow_sign
body: In the [[Cthulhu Mythos]], the [b]Yellow Sign[/b] is a symbol that is usually used by the Brotherhood of the Yellow Sign, a cult that worships the Great Old One [[Hastur]]. The Yellow Sign first appears in [[Robert W. Chambers]]' 1895 anthology [[The King in Yellow]].

title: command_input
body:
A visualization of the button sequence used to perform a special move in a video game. These inputs can be rendered either as visualizations of the input (-> A) or using numpad notation (6a). Most commonly found with 2D [[fighting game]]s.

h4. See also

* [[gameplay mechanics]]

title: peru
body:
A country in the South American continent. 

It is a megadiverse country with habitats ranging from the arid plains of the Pacific coastal region in the west to the peaks of the Andes mountains extending from the north to the southeast of the country to the tropical Amazon Basin rainforest in the east with the Amazon river.

It was home to several ancient cultures. Ranging from the Norte Chico civilization starting in 3500 BCE, the oldest civilization in the Americas and one of the five cradles of civilization, to the Inca Empire.

Its official language is [[spanish text|Spanish]] and Quechua.

h4. See also

* [[Incan]]
* [[Machu Picchu]] 
* [[Nazca lines]]

* "Wikipedia: Peru":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peru

title: ursaluna
body:
[[pokemon (creature)|Pokémon]] #0901 in the National Pokédex, a Ground/Normal-type.

Evolves from [[Ursaring]] (from [[Teddiursa]]) in Hisui. Notable for its role as a [[riding pokemon|Ride Pokémon]] in [[pokemon_legends:_arceus|Pokémon Legends: Arceus]].

A specific Ursaluna known as the [i]Bloodmoon Beast[/i] has a unique [[alternate form|form]] called [[Bloodmoon Ursaluna]].

Japanese name: [b]Gachiguma[/b]

title: crystal_maiden_(series)
body:
[b]Crystal Maidens[/b] is an H game published by [[Nutaku]] in 2019. The game shut down in 2022.

Crystal Maidens is a RPG, featuring "Maidens" as its characters. Players will have to spend ressources to upgrade their skills, craft equipments to further make them stronger, as well as manage the island's buildings. The game features gacha elements, as obtaining new maidens is purely RNG based.

h4. External Link: 
Discontinued Fandom Wiki: https://crystal-maidens.fandom.com/wiki/Crystal_Maidens_Wiki

title: lize_helesta
body:
A [[Nijisanji]] [[virtual YouTuber|VTuber]], part of the group [[Sanbaka (Nijisanji)|]] and designed by [[fuzichoco]]. 

She has [[long hair|long]] [[white hair|white]] with [[blue hair|blue]] [[colored inner hair]] and a blue [[gradient hair|gradient]] and [[purple eyes]]. Her regular hairstyle with her default outfit is [[flipped hair]] with [[blunt bangs]] and [[sidelocks]] decorated with a blue [[hairclip]].

Her background is that she is a [[princess]] of the Helesta kingdom, where her friend [[Ange Katrina]] also lives. The [[yellow bird]] with a [[monocle]] often seen on her head or shoulder is [[Sebastian Piyodore]], her butler. Due to a longstanding in-joke, [[Hanabatake Chaika]] is often depicted as her older brother.

title: ange_katrina
body:
A [[Nijisanji]] [[virtual YouTuber|VTuber]], part of the group [[Sanbaka (Nijisanji)|]] and designed by [[Kawaguchi (mojacome)|]].

She has [[red hair]] which is usually [[short hair|short]] with [[hair intakes]] and [[long bangs|long]] [[crossed bangs]] hanging [[hair between eyes|between her eyes]]. She often wears a [[triangle hair ornament]] or other triangle-themed jewelry.  Her eyes are [[blue eyes|blue]], sometimes with a distinct [[purple eyes|purple]] [[gradient eyes|gradient]], and she is depicted with either a [[flat chest]] or [[small breasts]].

Her background is that she is an [[alchemist]] living in the Helesta kingdom, where her friend [[Lize Helesta]] is royalty.

title: steel_massimo_(mega_man)
body:
[b]Series:[/b] [[Mega Man X (series)|]]

A playable character from [[Mega Man X: Command Mission]]. He's technically not the [i]original[/i] Steel Massimo. As his name suggests, Massimo is the tank character; he fights with huge axes and has vast reserves of HP (especially when he uses his Hyper Mode, Glint Armor).

title: detached_sleeves
body:
Sleeves that are detached from the main upper garment. 

Detached sleeves can be used with [[sleeveless]] or [[strapless]] outfits, since both tags only refer to the torso garment, which lacks attached sleeves in the first place.

h4. Examples
* !post #6385077: [[ribbon-trimmed sleeves]]
* !post #7533843: [[puffy detached sleeves]]

title: techno_baron
body:
Reoccurring antagonist who debuted in [[Shantae and the Pirate's Curse]]. One of the Barons of Sequin Land, thieving bandits who pass themselves off as artifact collectors.

He is a scheming technical genius who builds many weapons and gadgets of war, calling them "art". He engineers many of the weapons for the [[Ammo Baron]] with hopes that he can make enough money to take over Sequin Land himself. 

He is a small [[reptilian]] creature that wears a [[helmet]] mounted with [[gun]]s that [[covered_eyes|covers his eyes]], a [[black coat]] and purple [[waistcoat]].

title: twitch_(shantae)
body:
One of the few female soldiers in [[Ammo Baron]]'s army. 

Has [[blonde hair]], wears a [[white tank top]], [[blue skirt]], [[yellow gloves|yellow]] & [[black gloves|black]] [[fingerless gloves]] and a [[backpack]]. She wears [[green-tinted eyewear| green]] [[goggles]] and has a [[thigh holster]] for a comically oversized [[gun]]. Like the rest of the army she has a [[blue headwear|blue]] [[helmet]] that feature animalistic tails and ears, with the front of his featuring a [[:3]] face.

Always seen with [[Vinegar (shantae)|]]. Was a prototype design for [[Sky (shantae)|]] [tn]"[1]":[https://web.archive.org/web/20170908000516/https://www.themarysue.com/interview-with-shantae-co-creator-matt-bozon/][/tn].

title: pirate_master
body:
Main antagonist and final boss of [i][[Shantae and the Pirate's Curse]][/i]. 

[[Skeleton|Skeletal]], [[undead]] former mentor of [[Risky Boots]] and the former leader of the [[Tinkerbat]]s. Considered the greatest threat to Sequin Land, it took the combined power of every last Guardian Genie to defeat him and seal his bones in a secluded grave. From the great beyond he swore revenge against Risky Boots for her act of betrayal and theft of his weapons/crew during his final battle against the Genies.

Much of Risky Boots' equipment and even the skull she wears to cover herself originally belonged to him.

title: demae_itcho
body:
A brand of [[instant ramen]] by [[Nissin]], first releasing in 1968. The name means "one delivery order", referencing restaurant delivery orders for ramen and soba to awaiting customers elsewhere. The mascot, [[Demae Boy]], is seen carrying an [[okamochi (container)|]] for this purpose.

Traditionally sold in [[pack noodles|pack]] form, though [[cup ramen|cup]] forms were released later. One of the biggest Nissin brands in the Chinese/Hong Kong market, being more popular there than in Japan with tons of flavors, and internationally Nissin's choice for pack noodles (rendered as Demae Ramen overseas), except in the US due to [[Top Ramen]]'s existence.

h4. External links

* Piece of Japan: "The history and unknown story of Demae Ramen":[https://piece-of-japan.com/investing/instant-noodle/demae-ramen.html]
* SoraNews24: "We eat Chinese food inspired by Demae Itcho instant ramen to celebrate its 55-year anniversary":[https://soranews24.com/2023/02/17/we-eat-chinese-food-inspired-by-demae-itcho-instant-ramen-to-celebrate-its-55-year-anniversary/]
* TastesLab (Chinese): https://tasteslab.org/focus/20230308001

title: northampton_(azur_lane)
body:
[[Azur Lane]]'s personification of USS Northampton (CL/CA-26) which was the lead Northampton-class cruiser in service with the [[United States Navy]]. She was commissioned 17 May 1930 and sunk during the Battle of Tassafaronga on 1 December 1942.

Northampton has [[two-tone hair]], brown outside-cyan inside, lime-[[green eyes]], and [[dark skin]]. Her uniform consists of a white [[halterneck]] with a [[star (symbol)|star]] and a blue [[double vertical stripe]], and an assymetrical pair of white [[short shorts]]. She has a pair of [[red gloves]] and [[red footwear|red]] [[boots]]. In addition she has a [[compression sleeve]] on her left arm and a [[knee brace]] on her right leg.

Her [[rigging]] is exoskeleton-like with two mechanical braces, supporting two of her triple-[[ship turret|turrets]], while the third is hand-held.

title: pkp_pecheneg
body:
The PKP "Pecheneg" (Russian: Печенег) is a Russian machine gun chambered for the 7.62x54mmR round. It superseded the older [[pk machine gun|PK]] and [[PKM]] machine guns in Russian service in 2001.

It can be most easily distinguished from the earlier PKs by its carry handle - the PK and PKM have an L-shaped carry handle protruding above the receiver, while the PKP has an enclosed loop-shaped carry handle sitting flush at the same height as the receiver.

title: rapi_(nikke)
body:
A character in [[Goddess of Victory: Nikke]]. 

A member of the [[Counters (nikke)|]] squad along with [[Anis (nikke)|]] and [[Neon (nikke)|]], Rapi is usually protective, obedient, and an expressionless Nikke. 

She has [[orange eyes]], [[large breasts]] and [[long hair|long]] [[brown hair]]. She wears a [[black headwear|black]] [[beret]], [[black jacket|black]] [[cropped jacket]], [[black leotard|black]] [[collared leotard]], [[red necktie]], [[black gloves|black]] and [[red gloves|red]] [[two-tone gloves]], [[black thighhighs]], [[black footwear]], and a [[black choker]]. Usually depicted [[holding gun|holding]] or having an [[CZ 805 BREN]] [[assault rifle]] [[gun on back|on her back]].

[spoilers]Rapi was once a [[rapi (mass produced) (nikke)|Mass-produced Nikke]] with the serial number RR-15436. At some point in time, Rapi met [[Red Hood (nikke)|]], a former member of the legendary [[Goddess (nikke)|]] squad. When Red Hood died, Rapi somehow assimilated her entire body, more than doubling her mass and giving her a second core, a feat believed to be impossible. This has given her the ability to release immense heat from her body and intensifying her strength.[/spoilers]

[spoilers]Later she was upgraded and became a member of [[Absolute (Nikke)|]], Elysion's most powerful squad consisting (currently) of [[Emma (nikke)|]], [[Eunhwa (nikke)|]], and [[Vesti (nikke)|]]. However during a mission, one of Rapi's explosives killed a human, causing her to have an identity crisis. This led to Rapi leaving Absolute, much to her teammates dismay, and eventually joining the [[Counters (nikke)|]].[/spoilers]

Illustrators: [[Kim Hyung tae|Kim Hyung-tae]] and [[Hyulla]]
Voice actress: [[Kayli Mills]] (EN), [[Ishikawa Yui]] (JP)

title: sea_bunny
body:
Any kind of [[sea slug]] that vaguely looks like a [[rabbit]]. 

There is a species of sea slug, the [i]Jorunna parva[/i], which has the nickname of [i]sea bunny[/i] in several languages. The official Japanese name for it however is [i]sesame velvet sea slug[/i], due to its small spots and soft appearance. As a result, it is sometimes given the nickname goma-chan (sesame-chan).

title: prototype_sazabi
body:
A fictional manned giant robot from the [[Gundam]] [[mecha]]verse. It first appeared in [[Moon Gundam]].

[b]MSN-04X2 Sazabi Prototype (Terrain Mode)[/b]

A Newtype-use mobile suit designed for [[Neo Zeon]]'s new supreme commander, [[Char Aznable]]. It was envisioned as the culmination of the Neo Zeon-line MS and boasts incredible firepower in a single machine. 

The suit underwent several name changes, but in the end, it was given the name "Sazabi" by a developer who had kept the name to himself. As a result, it became a heavy mobile suit, one size larger than the Jagd Doga and the AMS-123X [[Varguil]] due to the required equipment, armaments and combat capability, in order to counter the [[Earth Federation]] Forces, which were reaching parity in material resources. 

This Sazabi Prototype (Terrain Mode) was one of the models used in assembling the MSN-04 [[Sazabi]] on the premise of the Earth Cooling Operation, so a AMS-119 [[Geara Doga]]'s cockpit core diverted to a two-seater type was temporarily installed in the torso. A Jagd Doga's head was attached as the head. The Long [[Beam Rifle]] with long range and high single-shot firepower was prepared as a handheld weapon.

title: shirakami_fubuki
body:
A [[Virtual YouTuber|VTuber]] and member of [[hololive]]'s [[1st generation (hololive)|]]. Also a member of [[hololive Gamers]]. Designed by [[Nagishiro Mito]]. On November 5th, 2020, Fubuki became the third member of hololive (after [[Gawr Gura]] and [[Inugami Korone]]) to reach 1 million subscribers on YouTube.

She is a white and black [[fox girl]] with [[fox ears]] with [[animal ear piercing|ear piercing]] on her left ear and a white and black-tipped [[fox tail]] with a [[pentagram]] inscription near the tip. She has [[aqua eyes]] and [[long hair|long]] [[white hair|white]] or [[grey hair|grey]] hair with an [[ahoge]] and [[double-parted bangs]] reaching [[hair between eyes|between her eyes]]. Her regular hairstyle consists of a [[low ponytail]] held with a [[black ribbon|black]] [[hair ribbon]], [[sidelocks]] and a [[side braid]].
