title: haaselia
body:
One of the members of the Evokers. An [[Harvin]] woman from [[Granblue Fantasy]]. The enlightened High Priestess, pact bearer to the Arcarum primal beast [[The Moon (granblue_fantasy)|]].

The resourceful and ingenious High Priestess wears an elegant smile, shrouding the clever deceit she keeps inside. She reached the breaking point of her pace when tragedy struck, transforming her festering enmity into a desire for revenge. Her heart now stained black, Haaselia is prepared to do whatever it takes to accomplish her goal even if it means deceiving those close to her.

The panel has since gained derivation.

title: wolf_guy:_ookami_no_monshou
body: Wolf Guy (ウルフガイ, Urufu Gai) is a Japanese manga series of two volumes published in 1970. The series had been readapted with a more violent and mature setting in 2007. This new adaptation, also known as Wolf Guy: Ōkami no Monshō, has been released as twelve volumes.

title: miracle_nikki
body:
The 3rd game of the [[Nikki (series)]] series, a Chinese mobile dress-up game series developed by Paper Studio. English server published by Elex, localized as Love Nikki: Dress-up Queen.

It uses very detailed and varied clothing, which artists sometimes use to create their on characters which they then draw.

It features gacha, crafting and drop mechanics, similar to personification games, as well as an actual storyline.

title: shadowheart_(baldur's_gate)
body:
One of the eight Origin characters in [[Baldur's Gate 3]] who can either be the player character or potential party member. An half-elf cleric of Shar, the goddess of darkness and loss. She was tasked to bring an artifact back to her cult, though she was stripped of her memories along with her true name. Despite her devotion to Shar, Shadowheart is surprisingly empathetic, being fond of children and having fewer qualms in providing assistance to others.

[spoilers]If pushed or persuaded to go against Shar, Shadowheart will learn the truth of her origins: Shadowheart wasn't raised to be a Sharran acolyte, but was born to and raised by worshippers of Selune, the goddess of the moon. She and her parents were kidnapped by Shar's zealots, with Shadowheart's memories being taken so that she could be molded into Shar's perfect champion. [/spoilers]

title: rick_dias
body:
A fictional [[mecha]] from the [[Gundam]] series. It first appeared in [[Zeta Gundam]].

[b]RMS-099 Rick Dias[/b]

The [[AEUG]]'s first original [[space]] combat "second generation" [[mobile suit]] design, taking in traditional aspects of [[Zeon]] MSs (the [[Rick Dom]] mostly) and pioneering new solutions such as the 360 degree monitors and the ejectable head-mounted cockpit. It was developed and produced by [[Anaheim Electronics]].

A red unit was initially piloted by [[Quattro Bajeena]], which sparked the fear of [[char_aznable|The Red Comet]] of old in the [[titans_(gundam)|Titans]]; once the AEUG became aware of this, all subsequent Rick Dias units moved on from the old black and grey (resembling the [[Dom (mobile suit)|]]) to the new red, so as to capitalize on the psychological impact of the color. Other notable AEUG Rick Dias pilots include Quattro's loyal wingmen: [[Apolly Bay]] and [[roberto_(gundam)|Roberto]]; [[Amuro Ray]], who piloted a red unit when he joined the Karaba/AEUG alliance; and [[Asuna Elmarit]], [[Ecole du Ciel]]'s main protagonist, who piloted a white unit as her first personal MS when she joined the AEUG.

After [[zeta_gundam|The Gryps War]] some red colored [[Schuzrum Dias]] variants were used by [[Neo Zeon]] during [[gundam_zz|The First Neo Zeon War]].

h4.Related MS development
* [[Rick Dias II]]
* [[Dijeh]]

body:
The true antagonist and final boss of [[Kirby & the Amazing Mirror]]. He shows himself after [[Kirby]] defeats [[Dark Meta Knight]] a second time. With help from [[Meta Knight]] and [[Shadow Kirby]], Kirby is able to defeat the dark tyrant with ease.

His resemblence to [[Nightmare (Kirby)|]] and [[Zero (kirby)|]] suggests that he may be a counterpart to Nightmare, [[Dark Matter (kirby)|]], or both. [spoiler][[void (kirby)|Void's]] ability to mimic him supports this theory.[/spoiler]

title: void_termina
body:
A dark, godlike creature appearing in [i][[Kirby Star Allies]][/i] as the true antagonist and final boss.

He is worshipped by [[Hyness]] [[francisca (kirby)|and]] [[flamberge (kirby)|his]] [[zan partizanne|underlings]] for reasons unknown beyond some kind of omnicidal revenge plot against an ancient civilization.

Ancient texts suggest that he only knows destruction and will carry it out with his mere existence. He is also apparently able to reincarnate from positive or negative energy. This information along with various patterns and designs shared by previous [i]Kirby[/i] villains suggests a heavy connection to [[Dark Matter (kirby)|]], [[Zero (kirby)|]] (and [[Zero Two (kirby)|]] by extension), the [[Master Crown]], and even [[Kirby]] himself.

However, since he is implied to be able to reincarnate with positive energy, it is possible for him to reawaken as a friend and provide protection and joy to the universe rather than its destructive end.

h4. Forms

* [[Void Termina (Demon God Form)|Demon God Form]]: A giant with arms, legs. and a mask.
* [[Void Termina (First Core)|First Core]]: A smaller inner form, that pulsates like a heart.
* [[Void Termina (Angel Form)|Angel Form]]: A giant like the Demon God Form, but its arms and legs are replaced with wings and a tail.
* [[Void Termina (Final Core)|Final Core]]: The final form, found within the First Core. It is a gooey pink sphere whose face morphs to resemble [[Kirby]] or entities related to [[Dark Matter (kirby)|]].

[spoiler]The Final Core has two alternative forms fought in [i]Star Allies'[/i] boss rush mode: [[Void Soul]] and [[Void (kirby)|]].[/spoiler]

title: shin'you_(kancolle)
body:
[[Kantai Collection]]'s personification of the Japanese escort carrier [i]Shin'you[/i]. Character designed by [[Shibafu (glock23)|]], voiced by [[Takao Kanon]].

Being originally German, she has  [[long hair|long]] [[blonde hair]] with [[blunt bangs]] and [[blue eyes]]. Her hair is tied to the left with a [[hair ornament]] that resembles a [[disposable cup]].

Her base outfit is almost identical to [[Kasuga Maru (Kancolle)|]]'s, wearing a white [[dougi]] top with a red [[hakama short skirt]], only to differentiate by wearing a yellow undershirt and [[yellow socks]] as opposed to Kasuga Maru's black.  On her left hand, she wears a thick falconry [[gloves|glove]]. 

The historical [i]Shin'you[/i] was originally the SS [i]Scarnhorst[/i], a German passenger liner. [i]Scharnhorst[/i] was stuck in Japan when [[World War II]] broke out in Europe. The Imperial Japanese Navy converted her into an escort carrier based on the plans for the [i]Taiyou[/i]-class carriers, much like [[Kasuga Maru (kancolle)|]]'s conversion. She was sunk in 1944 by torpedo attack from the submarine USS [i]Spadefish[/i].

Her [[abyssal ship|abyssal]] form is assumed to be the [[German Escort Princess]].

title: hachijou_(kancolle)
body:
[[Kantai Collection]]'s personification of the Japanese escort ship [i]Hachijou[/i]. Character design by [[Ugume]], voiced by [[Takao Kanon]]. 

She has [[short_hair|short]] [[brown hair]] tied by [[black ribbon|black]] [[hair ribbon]]s, and [[blue eyes]]. Her default outfit is the class' uniform: a [[white shirt]], [[fur-trimmed jacket|fur-trimmed]] [[green jacket]], [[red ribbon|red]] [[neck ribbon]], [[green skirt|green]] [[pleated skirt]], [[white socks]], and [[black footwear|black]] [[mary janes]]. 

Her [[rigging]] consists of her funnel and foremast to her back, two hull pieces each containing a 12 cm single gun mount and 25 mm triple [[anti-aircraft gun]]s, and [[depth charge]]s on her ankles. 

The historical [i]IJN Hachijou[/i] was commissioned in late March 1941, mostly patrolling the northern waters of Japan and escorted convoys. She survived an air attack in July 1944 and went on to survive the war, although she was scrapped in 1948 apparently having sat idle by that time.

title: senkou_hanabi_dan_(idolmaster)
body:
Flash☆HANABI Squad, or Senkou☆HANABI Dan in Japanese, is a unit that appears in the smartphone app [[Idolmaster Million Live! Theater Days]].

The unit consists of the following five members:
* [[Takayama Sayoko]]  (CV:[[Komagata Yui]])
* [[Yokoyama Nao]]  (CV:[[Watanabe Yui]])
* [[Kousaka Umi]]  (CV:[[Ueda Reina]])
* [[Satake Minako]] (CV:[[Ozeki Eri]])
* [[Fukuda Noriko]] (CV:[[Hamasaki Nana]])

They are the only five-member unit in the Idolmaster Million Live! series. They also perform a song named “Flash☆HANABI Squad”. This unit is very popular among fans of the Idolmaster Million Live! series.

title: friend_inside_me_(meme)
body:
Reference to a post made by Toby Fox on Tumblr, in which he posted an audio edit of the song "You've Got a Friend in Me" from [[Toy Story]], becoming lower in key and repeating the phrase "Friend inside me". Some believe that the song will be referenced in [[Deltarune]] in some way, invoking the (misconceived belief that a) similar joke song, "A Baby Legend" from the cancelled sequel to the mpreg Homestuck joke album "The Baby Is You", "The Baby is 2", was referenced in [[Pokemon SwSh]] through the Battle Tower theme.

h4. External links

* fwugradiation's Tumblr: "friend inside me":[https://fwugradiation.tumblr.com/post/187904005186/friend-inside-me]
* Know Your Meme: "Friend Inside Me":[https://knowyourmeme.com/memes/friend-inside-me]

title: nearl_(arknights)
body:
[i]Nearl, former knight of Kazimierz, is a core member on the battlefield with her defense and healing skills.[/i]

A playable Defender Operator in [[Arknights]].

Real Name: Margaret Nearl

h4. Profile
[expand]
[table]
[tbody]
      [tr][td]Place of Birth:[/td]
      [td]Kazimierz[/td][/tr]
      [tr][td]Birthday:[/td]
      [td]April 23[/td][/tr]
      [tr][td]Race:[/td]
      [td]Kuranta[/td][/tr]
      [tr][td]Height:[/td]
      [td]171 cm[/td][/tr]
      [tr][td]Combat Experience:[/td]
      [td]5 years[/td][/tr]
  [/tbody]
[/table]
[/expand]

A member of the Infected support group, "Followers". She has demonstrated remarkable combat techniques and military discipline, whether it be covering allies, mobile warfare, all-out assault or field battle. Currently a heavy-weapon Operator for Rhodes Island and provides command and in-person combat support.

Her motif is based on the [[Pegasus]].

Her [[voice actor]] is [[Sakura Ayane]].

h5. Related Operators
* [[Blemishine (Arknights)|]] - Little sister
* [[Whislash (Arknights)|]] - Auntie
* [[Mlynar (Arknights)|]] - Uncle

title: unworn_hair_ornament
body:
When a character is not wearing (a) [[hair ornament]](s) they usually wear, but said hair ornament(s) is/are still present in the picture. If a character has not removed all their hair ornaments, it still counts, as long as at least one of the removed hair ornaments is still present.

Something like post #6576289 does not count, because in that post, Chiaki is still wearing her spaceship hair ornament. The artist just made the stylistic choice to include multiple representations of it in the picture.

title: nanami_chiaki
body:
Character from [[Danganronpa 2: Goodbye Despair]]. Her title is Ultimate Gamer (超高校級の「ゲーマー」).

She has [[flipped hair|flipped]] pink or light brown [[medium hair]] with a [[Galaga]] [[hairclip]], and pink eyes. She wears a [[pleated skirt|pleated]] [[brown skirt]], [[black thighhighs|black]] [[over-kneehighs]], a [[pink ribbon|pink]] [[neck ribbon]], and a black and white [[dress shirt|dress]] [[collared shirt|shirt]] that is [[shirt tucked in|tucked]] in her skirt. She has a [[hooded jacket]] that's shaped like a [[cat hood]] and she carries a pink [[backpack]], that's shaped like a [[cat bag]]. 

As the Ultimate Gamer, she loves video games of all kinds, and playing so many games has given her a wide range of general knowledge. Because of this you mostly see her [[holding handheld game console|holding and playing on a handheld game console]]. She's playing [[Galaga|Galaga Omega]] for the most time of the day and wears a hair ornament dedicated to the game. When she's not with [[Hinata Hajime|Hinata]] or [[Komaeda Nagito|Nagito]], she's sometimes seen with [[Monomi (Danganronpa)|]] by her side.

[spoiler]In Danganronpa 2: Goodbye Despair she is actually an artificial intelligence. Her creator and "father" was [[Fujisaki Chihiro]], the Ultimate Programmer from [[Danganronpa: Trigger Happy Havoc]] who programmed her A.I. for the Neo World Program.

[[Danganronpa 3 (anime)|]] reveals her to be based off of an actual Nanami Chiaki, who was part of Class 77-B and was executed by [[Enoshima Junko]] to push the rest of the class into despair. In this show she's wearing the [[Hope's Peak Academy School Uniform]]. She also wears [[loafers]] instead of [[mary janes]].[/spoiler]

Like other Danganronpa Girls, she has an official [[Playboy bunny]] outfit. She wears a [[two-tone leotard|two-tone]] [[white leotard|white]] and [[black leotard]], [[fishnet thighhighs]] and a [[rabbit hood|bunny hood]] with [[fake animal ears|fake]] [[rabbit ears|bunny ears]].

title: head_bump
body:
A usually exaggerated swelling on the head caused by minor [[injury]] to it. Most frequently used for comedic effect, either to make depictions of physical violence in light-hearted material more palatable, or to indicate a character has been punished for some action without having to actually depict the punishment. They seldom last longer than one scene, and virtually never represent serious injuries.

Frequently appears in conjunction with [[crossed bandaids]]. If someone is bumping their head against another person's head, use [[headbutt]] instead.

title: marley_(pokemon)
body:
[b]Marley[/b], known as [b]Mai[/b] (マイ) in Japan, is a character introduced in [i][[pokemon|Pokémon]] [[pokemon dppt|Diamond and Pearl]][/i].

She doesn't speak much and seems mysterious, but she simply doesn't like to talk and is really a Trainer with a kind heart who cares about both people and Pokémon.

She has [[blue eyes]] and [[short hair|short]] [[black hair]]. She wears a [[short dress|short]] [[black dress]], [[black pantyhose]], and [[black footwear|black]] [[boots]].

For her [i][[Pokemon Legends: Arceus]][/i] counterpart, see [[Mai (Pokemon)]] 

h4. Official Art
* !post #4404097

h4. External links

* "Bulbapedia: Marley":[https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Marley]

title: black_sun
body:
A [[sun]] that is colored black, typically associated with [[Reiuji Utsuho]]. 

Not to be confused with:

* A [[solar eclipse]], which creates a radial corona around the star.
* A [[black hole]], which creates a Φ-shaped accretion disk.
* The [[darksign (dark_souls)|]] symbol from [[Dark Souls (Series)|]].
* The [[Black Sun (symbol)|]] (Sonnenrad) symbol used by the [[Waffen-SS]] during World War II.
* [[Kamen Rider Black Sun (Series)|]], a modernized reimagining of [[Kamen Rider Black (Series)|]], or its [[Kamen Rider Black Sun|titular character]].

title: takuan
body:

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: Takuan":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Takuan

title: martini
body:
A classic [[cocktail]] made with gin (or less traditionally, [[vodka]]) and a splash of vermouth, often garnished with an [[olive]]. Its popularity and longevity have resulted in the [[cocktail glass]] being informally known as a "martini glass", and a number of otherwise unrelated drinks reference the martini in their name (e.g. appletini, chocolate martini).

h4. See also

* [[Tag Group:Food Tags]]

title: margarita
body:
A sweet [[tequila]]-based [[cocktail]], usually flavored with [[lime (fruit)|]] juice and orange liqueur. It is typically served in a distinctive stemmed glass with a short bowl reminiscent of a [[champagne coupe]]. The rim of the glass is often garnished with [[salt]].

h4. See also

* [[Tag Group:Food Tags]]
other_names: マルガリータ(カクテル)

title: teacher
body:
A person who teaches students in a [[school]].

The stereotypical depiction of a teacher wears a [[skirt suit]] and carries a [[pointer]]. Use this tag when a character is dressed or portrayed as a teacher, not just when they canonically work as a teacher.

title: amaterasu_(ookami)
body:
[b]Amaterasu[/b] ([b]天照[/b]), nicknamed [b]Ammy[/b] by [[Issun]], is the main protagonist of [[Ookami (game)|]]. In her past life she was known as [[Shiranui (ookami)|]]. Amaterasu is the Ōkami, the Sun Goddess to all of Nippon, and the "[i]origin of all that is good and mother to us all[/i]".

She wields 3 divine instruments: a [[reflector_(ookami)|]] ([[shield]]), a [[rosary_(ookami)|]] (string of [[magatama]] beads), and a [[glaive_(ookami)|]] ([[sword]]).

A popular practice for fans of [i]Okami[/i] is to draw what one would assume a {{amaterasu_(ookami) personification|human Amaterasu would look like}}. Many variations exist.

She has a son, [[Chibiterasu]], who is the protagonist of [[Ookamiden]].

title: momoe_nagisa
body:
A character from [i][[Mahou Shoujo Madoka Magica]][/i], introduced in the [[mahou shoujo madoka magica: hangyaku no monogatari|third movie.]]

She has [[long hair|long]] [[white hair]] in [[two side up|two sides up]] and [[multicolored eyes|multicolored]] [[ringed eyes]]. Her regular clothes is a [[sailor dress]] with [[polka dot dress| polka dots]] and a [[pantyhose]]. She is very fond of [[cheese]].

In her [[magical girl]] form, she wears a [[capelet]] with [[suspenders]], [[fingerless gloves]], a [[beanie]] with [[pom_pom_(clothes)|poms poms]] and [[fake animal ears]], a [[fur trim]]  and a [[bubble skirt]] with a [[polka dot legwear|polka dot]] pantyhose. Her weapon is a [[trumpet]] that can release explosive [[bubble]]s.  

[spoiler]She is actually the original magical girl who became the witch [[Charlotte (Madoka Magica)|Charlotte]].[/spoiler]

h4. Appearance

body:
When the forehead of a character is touched either by [[hand on own head|themselves]] or by another character, using either a finger or a hand.

Not to be confused with [[forehead-to-forehead]], where the forehead of a character touches the forehead of another.
